You can use `{upsert:true}` option as follows

    cModel.update({ name: { $regex: new RegExp(`^${company.name}$`, &#39;i&#39;) } }        
    , company, { upsert: true }, function(err, res) { 
        // Deal with the response data/error
    });

So it will update if the document exists, else it will insert as new document. If you want the newly created doc in response use `{new:true}`

you can use `upsert: true` option to insert doc into collection if the id doesn&#39;t exist in collection, also use `$setOnInsert` to set data only when an `upsert` occur 

Example : 

    model.update({id: id},
            {
                &quot;$set&quot;: data,
                &quot;$setOnInsert&quot;: upsertData,
            },
            {upsert: true});

